===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|descreistre|lang=fro}} (French: {{term|décroître|lang=fr}}), from {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|decrescere|lang=la}}.

===Verb===
{{en-verb|decreas|ing}}

# {{intransitive}} Of a quantity, to become [[smaller]].
# {{transitive}} To make (a quantity) smaller.

====Synonyms====
* {{sense|become smaller}} [[drop]], [[fall]], [[go down]], [[plummet]] (''rapidly''), [[plunge]] (''rapidly''), [[reduce]], [[shrink]], [[sink]]
* {{sense|make smaller}} [[abate]], [[cut]], [[decrement]], [[lower]], [[reduce]]

====Antonyms====
* {{sense|become larger}} [[go up]], [[grow]], [[increase]], [[rise]], [[soar]] (''rapidly''), [[shoot up]] (''rapidly'')
* {{sense|make larger}} [[increase]], [[increment]], [[raise]], [[up]] {{qualifier|informal}}

